.TH BW 1 "2025-10-28" "Bitwarden CLI" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bw \- Bitwarden command-line interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bw
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.IR command
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Bitwarden CLI is a powerful, full-featured command-line interface (CLI)
tool to access and manage a Bitwarden vault. The CLI is written with
TypeScript and Node.js and can be used to access and manage your Bitwarden
vault from the terminal.
.PP
Bitwarden is a free and open-source password management service that stores
sensitive information such as website credentials in an encrypted vault.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B login
Log into a user account.
.TP
.B logout
Log out of the current user account.
.TP
.B unlock
Unlock the vault.
.TP
.B lock
Lock the vault.
.TP
.B sync
Sync the vault with the server.
.TP
.B list
List items in the vault (items, folders, collections, organizations).
.TP
.B get
Get an item from the vault.
.TP
.B create
Create a new item in the vault.
.TP
.B edit
Edit an existing item in the vault.
.TP
.B delete
Delete an item from the vault.
.TP
.B restore
Restore a deleted item.
.TP
.B share
Share an item with an organization.
.TP
.B confirm
Confirm a user to an organization.
.TP
.B import
Import vault data from a file.
.TP
.B export
Export vault data to a file.
.TP
.B generate
Generate a password or passphrase.
.TP
.B encode
Base64 encode a string.
.TP
.B config
Configure CLI settings.
.TP
.B update
Check for updates to the CLI.
.TP
.B status
Show vault status.
.TP
.B serve
Start a RESTful API webserver.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help information.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information.
.TP
.B \-\-pretty
Format output with indentation and line breaks.
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Return raw output with minimal formatting.
.TP
.B \-\-response
Return a JSON formatted response.
.TP
.B \-\-session <session>
Pass session key instead of reading from environment.
.TP
.B \-\-apikey
Use API key authentication.
.TP
.B \-\-nointeraction
Do not prompt for interactive input.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BW_SESSION
Session key for authenticated commands. Set this environment variable
to avoid having to pass \fB\-\-session\fR with each command.
.TP
.B BW_CLIENTID
Client ID for API key authentication.
.TP
.B BW_CLIENTSECRET
Client secret for API key authentication.
.TP
.B BW_PASSWORD
Master password (use with caution).
.TP
.B BW_SERVE_HOSTNAME
Hostname for serve command (default: localhost).
.TP
.B BW_SERVE_PORT
Port for serve command (default: 8087).
.TP
.B BW_RESPONSE
Set to "true" to enable JSON response format by default.
.TP
.B BW_CLEANEXIT
Set to "true" to always exit with code 0.
.TP
.B BW_QUIET
Suppress output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Log in to your Bitwarden account:
.B bw login
.TP
Unlock your vault:
.B bw unlock
.TP
List all items in your vault:
.B bw list items
.TP
Get a specific item by ID:
.B bw get item <item-id>
.TP
Generate a password:
.B bw generate \-\-length 20 \-\-uppercase \-\-lowercase \-\-number \-\-special
.TP
Export vault data:
.B bw export \-\-output /path/to/export.json
.TP
Start the API server:
.B bw serve
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/Bitwarden\ CLI/data.json
Default location for vault data.
